data.enText: to provide sb with a different home to live in

data.chText: 数千名地震灾民仍在等待安排新住处。
data.enText: Thousands of earthquake victims are still waiting to be rehoused.

tr: put up in a new or different housing

value.def: If someone is rehoused, their council, local government, or other authority provides them with a different house to live in.

example.ex: Many of the 100,000 or so families who lost their homes in the earthquake have still not been rehoused...
example.tran: 有10万户左右的家庭在地震中失去了家园，其中许多家庭还没有得到安置。

example.ex: The council has agreed to rehouse the family.
example.tran: 委员会同意给这个家庭重新安排住房。
